author: DAVE BYRNE | Sports Writer
title: Girls soccer: Plenty of unanswered questions as L-L girls enter final week of regular season.
text:
Buy Now DAN MARSCHKA | Staff Photographer 
As we enter the final week of the Lancaster-Lebanon League girls soccer regular season the section title races are somewhat unsettled. 
The playoffs, which begin Saturday with quarterfinal matches, not so much. 
This being an "odd-numbered" year, three spots each are reserved for teams from Sections One and Three with two teams from Section Two rounding out the field of eight. 
Conestoga Valley, Hempfield and Manheim Township, although not necessarily in that order, are the trio from Section One. 
Elco and Donegal have two of the three Section Three berths staked out. The thrd slot is a jump ball between Pequea Valley, Annville-Cleona and Lancaster Mennonite. 
With the Section Two title pretty much in hand, Elizabethtown is in from Section Two. Joining the Bears? 
With two matches remaining on the schedule four teams can still consider themselves contenders for the remaining playoff invitation. 
Cocalico and Ephrata are currently tied for second — they meet Tuesday, in Denver, in a match moved from Monday to accommodate a scheduling conflict — with Lampeter-Strasburg and Manheim Central still with an outside shot. 
After facing each other on Tuesday, Cocalico (8-2-1, 25 points) and Ephrata (8-3-1, 25 points) finish Wednesday with Cocalico at Lebanon (0-12) and Ephrata hosting Garden Spot (4-7). The Eagles also have a makeup match at Garden Spot still outstanding. 
L-S (7-5, 21) hosts Manheim (6-3-2, 20) on Monday. The Pioneers host E-town (10-1, 30) on Wednesday while Manheim hosts Solanco (1-11). 
With the Section Three title all but clinched, after defeating Donegal on Wednesday, Elco (10-1-1, 31) got bushwhacked by Lancaster Mennonite Friday , as the Blazers battled the Raiders to a 0-0 tie 
It's within the realm of possibility that Donegal (9-2, 27) could slip past Elco. With a road trip to Annville-Cleona (6-5) still on the books, the Indians travel to Mennonite (5-5) Monday and host Pequea Valley (6-5-1) Wednesday. 
Elco, meanwhile, finishes with Lebanon Catholic (2-10) at home and travels to Lancaster Catholic (3-9). 
Who will win Section One? 
As of this moment, Manheim Township (8-1-1, 25) has a razor's edge on Conestoga Valley (8-2, 24) and Hempfield (7-2-1, 22). 
Township travels to Hempfield Tuesday evening and finishes at home Thursday with Penn Manor (3-7-1). 
CV hosts Cedar Crest (5-4-1) Tuesday — the Falcons were eliminated from playoff contention Saturday with a 2-0 loss to Township — before closing out the schedule at Hempfield on Thursday. More Headlines
